{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c8e-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6041"},"text":"§ 6041.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Information at source","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c8f-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Payments exceeding threshold","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"All persons engaged in a trade or business and making payment in the course of such trade or business to another person, of rent, salaries, wages, premiums, annuities, compensations, remunerations, emoluments, or other fixed or determinable gains, profits, and income (other than payments to which section 6042(a)(1), 6044(a)(1), 6047(e), 6049(a), or 6050N(a) applies, and other than payments with respect to which a statement is required under the authority of section 6042(a)(2), 6044(a)(2), or 6045), of $2,000 or more in any calendar year, or, in the case of such payments made by the United States, the officers or employees of the United States having information as to such payments and required to make returns in regard thereto by the regulations hereinafter provided for, shall render a true and accurate return to the Secretary, under such regulations and in such form and manner and to such extent as may be prescribed by the Secretary, setting forth the amount of such gains, profits, and income (including a separate accounting of any such amounts reasonably designated as cash tips and the occupation described in section 224(d)(1) of the person receiving such tips and a separate accounting of any amount of qualified overtime compensation (as defined in section 225(c))), and the name and address of the recipient of such payment.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c90-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Collection of foreign items","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of collections of items (not payable in the United States) of interest upon the bonds of foreign countries and interest upon the bonds of and dividends from foreign corporations by any person undertaking as a matter of business or for profit the collection of foreign payments of such interest or dividends by means of coupons, checks, or bills of exchange, such person shall make a return according to the forms or regulations prescribed by the Secretary, setting forth the amount paid and the name and address of the recipient of each such payment.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c91-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Recipient to furnish name and address","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"When necessary to make effective the provisions of this section, the name and address of the recipient of income shall be furnished upon demand of the person paying the income.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c92-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Statements to be furnished to persons with respect to whom information is required","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Every person required to make a return under subsection (a) shall furnish to each person with respect to whom such a return is required a written statement showing—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c93-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the name, address, and phone number of the information contact of the person required to make such return,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c94-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the aggregate amount of payments to the person required to be shown on the return,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c95-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of compensation to non-employees, the portion of payments that have been reasonably designated as cash tips and the occupation described in section 224(d)(1) of the person receiving such tips, and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c96-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/d/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the portion of payments that are qualified overtime compensation (as defined in section 225(c)).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"The written statement required under the preceding sentence shall be furnished to the person on or before January 31 of the year following the calendar year for which the return under subsection (a) was required to be made. To the extent provided in regulations prescribed by the Secretary, this subsection shall also apply to persons required to make returns under subsection (b).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c97-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Section does not apply to certain tips","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This section shall not apply to tips with respect to which section 6053(a) (relating to reporting of tips) applies.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c98-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Section does not apply to certain health arrangements","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"This section shall not apply to any payment for medical care (as defined in section 213(d)) made under—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c99-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/f/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a flexible spending arrangement (as defined in section 106(c)(2)), or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c9a-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/f/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a health reimbursement arrangement which is treated as employer-provided coverage under an accident or health plan for purposes of section 106.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c9b-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Nonqualified deferred compensation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (a) shall apply to—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c9c-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/g/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any deferrals for the year under a nonqualified deferred compensation plan (within the meaning of section 409A(d)), whether or not paid, except that this paragraph shall not apply to deferrals which are required to be reported under section 6051(a)(13) (without regard to any de minimis exception), and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c9d-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/g/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any amount includible under section 409A and which is not treated as wages under section 3401(a).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c9e-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/h"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"h"},"text":"(h)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Inflation adjustment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of any calendar year after 2026, the dollar amount in subsection (a) shall be increased by an amount equal to—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id466e7c9f-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/h/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" such dollar amount, multiplied by","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id466e7ca0-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s6041/h/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the cost-of-living adjustment determined under section 1(f)(3) for such calendar year, determined by substituting “calendar year 2025” for “calendar year 2016” in subparagraph (A)(ii) thereof.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"If any increase under the preceding sentence is not a multiple of $100, such increase shall be rounded to the nearest multiple of $100.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id466e7ca1-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736"},"text":"Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68A/745"},"text":"68A Stat. 745","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/834/s19/f"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–834, § 19(f)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-10-16"},"text":"Oct. 16, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/1058"},"text":"76 Stat. 1058","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/tXIX/s1906/b/13/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, title XIX, § 1906(b)(13)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-04"},"text":"Oct. 4, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/1834"},"text":"90 Stat. 1834","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/600/tV/s501/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–600, title V, § 501(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2878"},"text":"92 Stat. 2878","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/34/tVII/s723/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–34, title VII, § 723(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/344"},"text":"95 Stat. 344","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/248/tIII/s309/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–248, title III, § 309(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-03"},"text":"Sept. 3, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/595"},"text":"96 Stat. 595","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/dA/tVII/s722/h/4/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, div. A, title VII, § 722(h)(4)(B)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-07-18"},"text":"July 18, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/976"},"text":"98 Stat. 976","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/tXV"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, title XV","children":[],"tail":", §§ 1501(c)(1), 1523(b)(2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/2736"},"text":"100 Stat. 2736","children":[],"tail":", 2748; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/168/tXII/s1201/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–168, title XII, § 1201(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-07-30"},"text":"July 30, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/1469"},"text":"110 Stat. 1469","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/173/tXII/s1203/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–173, title XII, § 1203(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-12-08"},"text":"Dec. 8, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/2480"},"text":"117 Stat. 2480","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/357/tVIII/s885/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–357, title VIII, § 885(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/1640"},"text":"118 Stat. 1640","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/148/tIX/s9006/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–148, title IX, § 9006(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-03-23"},"text":"Mar. 23, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/855"},"text":"124 Stat. 855","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/240/tII/s2101/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–240, title II, § 2101(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-09-27"},"text":"Sept. 27, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/2561"},"text":"124 Stat. 2561","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/9"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–9","children":[],"tail":", §§ 2(a), (b), 3(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-04-14"},"text":"Apr. 14, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/125/36"},"text":"125 Stat. 36","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/21/tVII"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–21, title VII","children":[],"tail":", §§ 70201(f)(1), 70202(c)(2), 70433(a), (b), (e), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-07-04"},"text":"July 4, 2025","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/139/172"},"text":"139 Stat. 172","children":[],"tail":", 175, 243, 244.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id466e7ca2-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id466e7ca3-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id466e7ca4-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2025—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/21/s70433/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–21, § 70433(e)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “exceeding threshold” for “of $600 or more” in heading and “calendar year” for “taxable year” in text."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/21/s70433/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–21, § 70433(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “$2,000” for “$600”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/21/s70202/c/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–21, § 70202(c)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", which directed the insertion of “and a separate accounting of any amount of qualified overtime compensation (as defined in section 225(c))” after “occupation of the person receiving such tips”, was executed by making the insertion after “occupation described in section 224(d)(1) of the person receiving such tips”, to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/21/s70201/f/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–21, § 70201(f)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “(including a separate accounting of any such amounts reasonably designated as cash tips and the occupation described in section 224(d)(1) of the person receiving such tips)” after “such gains, profits, and income”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/21/s70201/f/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–21, § 70201(f)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (3)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/21/s70202/c/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–21, § 70202(c)(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (h). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/21/s70433/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–21, § 70433(b)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (h)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2011—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/9/s2/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–9, § 2(b)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “amounts in consideration for property,” after “salaries, wages,”, “gross proceeds,” after “emoluments, or other”, and “gross proceeds,” after “setting forth the amount of such”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (h). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/9/s3/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–9, § 3(a)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (h) which related to treatment of rental property expense payments."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (i), (j). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/9/s2/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–9, § 2(a)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsecs. (i) and (j) which read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(i) ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Application to Corporations","children":[],"tail":".—Notwithstanding any regulation prescribed by the Secretary before the date of the enactment of this subsection, for purposes of this section the term ‘person’ includes any corporation that is not an organization exempt from tax under section 501(a)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(j) ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Regulations","children":[],"tail":".—The Secretary may prescribe such regulations and other guidance as may be appropriate or necessary to carry out the purposes of this section, including rules to prevent duplicative reporting of transactions.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2010—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/148/s9006/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–148, § 9006(b)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “amounts in consideration for property,” after “salaries, wages,”, “gross proceeds,” after “emoluments, or other”, and “gross proceeds,” after “setting forth the amount of such”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (h). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/240"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–240","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (h). Former subsec. (h) redesignated (i)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/148/s9006/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–148, § 9006(a)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (h)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (i). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/240"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–240","children":[],"tail":" redesignated subsec. (h) as (i). Former subsec. (i) redesignated (j)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/148/s9006/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–148, § 9006(a)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (i)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (j). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/240"